{"timestamp": "2026-05-27 18:03:21,687", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_validation_result", "line": 185, "message": "{\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-27T18:03:21.687189\", \"task_id\": \"unknown\", \"task_objective\": \"Implement the Job Description Parsing module that ingests and structures job requirements.\", \"result\": \"```python\\nimport re\\n\\nclass JobDescriptionParser:\\n    def __init__(self, job_description_text):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Initializes the JobDescriptionParser with the job description text.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            job_description_text (str): The raw text of the job description.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.job_description_text = job_description_text\\n        self.parsed_data = {}\\n\\n    def extract_job_title(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Extracts the job title from the job description text using regex.\\n      ...\", \"validation_type\": \"text\", \"status\": \"completed\", \"feedback\": \"here are some feedbacks:\\n1. The current regex patterns stop at the first newline, so they only capture single-line content. Multiline sections (like job summary or skills listed on multiple lines) aren’t fully captured.\\n2. The code doesn’t generalize well if the order of sections changes or if there are additional blank lines.\\n3. It would be clearer and more robust to locate each section by its heading and grab everything up to the next heading or end of text.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\nimport re\\n\\nclass JobDescriptionParser:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Parses a raw job description text into structured fields:\\n      - job_title\\n      - job_summary\\n      - required_skills\\n      - experience_level\\n      - education_requirements\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    SECTION_PATTERNS = {\\n        'job_title':       r\\\"(?:Job Title|Title|Position)\\\\s*:\\\\s*(?P<content>.+)\\\",\\n        'job_summary':     r\\\"(?:Job Summary|Job Description|Summary)\\\\s*:\\\\s*(?P<content>.*?)(?=\\\\n[A-Z][A-Za-z ]+?:|\\\\Z)\\\",\\n        'required_skills': r\\\"(?:Skills|Required Skills|Technical Skills)\\\\s*:\\\\s*(?P<content>.*?)(?=\\\\n[A-Z][A-Za-z ]+?:|\\\\Z)\\\",\\n        'experience_level':r\\\"(?:Experience|Experience Level)\\\\s*:\\\\s*(?P<content>.*?)(?=\\\\n[A-Z][A-Za-z ]+?:|\\\\Z)\\\",\\n        'education_requirements':\\n                           r\\\"(?:Education|Education Requirements|Qualifications)\\\\s*:\\\\s*(?P<content>.*?)(?=\\\\n[A-Z][A-Za-z ]+?:|\\\\Z)\\\",\\n    }\\n\\n    def __init__(self, text):\\n        self.text = text.strip()\\n        self.parsed = {}\\n\\n    def _extract_section(self, key, pattern, multiline=False):\\n        flags = re.IGNORECASE | (re.DOTALL if multiline else 0)\\n        match = re.search(pattern, self.text, flags)\\n        if not match:\\n            return None\\n        content = match.group('content').strip()\\n        return content\\n\\n    def parse(self):\\n        # Extract each section\\n        for key, pat in self.SECTION_PATTERNS.items():\\n            # summary, skills, experience, education may be multiline\\n            is_multi = key in ('job_summary', 'required_skills',\\n                               'experience_level', 'education_requirements')\\n            raw = self._extract_section(key, pat, multiline=is_multi)\\n            if key == 'required_skills' and raw:\\n                # Split on bullets, commas, semicolons, or newlines\\n                items = re.split(r\\\"[\\\\n,;•\\\\-]+\\\", raw)\\n                self.parsed[key] = [item.strip() for item in items if item.strip()]\\n            else:\\n                self.parsed[key] = raw\\n        return self.parsed\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    example = \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Job Title: Senior Software Engineer\\n\\n    Job Summary:\\n    We are looking for a Senior Software Engineer to develop high-quality software,\\n    collaborate with cross-functional teams, and mentor junior engineers.\\n\\n    Required Skills:\\n    - Python\\n    - Django\\n    - PostgreSQL\\n    - REST API design\\n\\n    Experience: 5+ years\\n\\n    Education: Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or related field\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    parser = JobDescriptionParser(example)\\n    result = parser.parse()\\n    print(result)\\n```\\n\\nExplanation of changes:\\n- Defined `SECTION_PATTERNS` mapping field keys to regex that captures everything until the next heading (lookahead on capitalized line ending with `:`) or end of text.\\n- The `_extract_section` method applies DOTALL only when needed for multiline sections.\\n- For `required_skills`, splits the captured block into a cleaned list.\\n- Ensures each section is captured in full, regardless of blank lines or ordering.\"}"}
