o evaluate responses.\\\",\\n        \\\"8. Send Thank-You Email: Send email to candidate (Email Notification Service - task3).\\\",\\n        \\\"9. Generate Evaluation Report: Summarize qualifications, interview performance, and suitability.\\\",\\n        \\\"10. Send Report to Hiring Manager: Send report to hiring manager (Email Notification Service - task3).\\\"\\n    ]\\n    return steps\\n\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    # Example usage with sample questions\\n    sample_questions = [\\n        {\\\"id\\\": \\\"q1\\\", \\\"question\\\": \\\"What is a Python list comprehension?\\\"},\\n        {\\n            \\\"id\\\": \\\"q2\\\",\\n            \\\"question\\\": \\\"Explain the difference between a list and a tuple.\\\",\\n            \\\"options\\\": [\\n                \\\"Lists are immutable, tuples are mutable\\\",\\n                \\\"Lists are mutable, tuples are immutable\\\",\\n                \\\"Both are immutable\\\",\\n                \\\"Both are mutable\\\",\\n            ],\\n        },\\n        {\\\"id\\\": \\\"q3\\\", \\\"question\\\": \\\"Write a function to reverse a string in Python.\\\"},\\n    ]\\n\\n    interface = TechnicalInterviewInterface(sample_questions)\\n    responses = interface.conduct_interview()\\n    print(\\\"Captured Responses:\\\")\\n    print(json.dumps(responses, indent=2))\\n\\n    # Optionally save to file\\n    interface.save_responses(\\\"candidate_responses.json\\\")\\n\\n    # Generate workflow steps and save to file\\n    steps = workflow()\\n    with open(\\\"technical_interview_workflow.txt\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n        for step in steps:\\n            f.write(step + \\\"\\\\n\\\")\\n    print(\\\"\\\\nTechnical interview workflow steps saved to technical_interview_workflow.txt\\\")\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## FEEDBACK to VERSION 4\\nhere are some feedbacks:\\n- The `workflow()` function and .txt file writing are extraneous to the current 